#ygkc

full_text: Mayor Paterson: We've had a good round of questions from council, at this point we'll open it up to attendees. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b"Mayor Paterson: We've had a good round of questions from council, at this point we'll open it up to attendees. #ygkc"

full_text:
Coun. Doherty: Are there some municipalities in Ontario that you would hold up as best practices?
Saxe: Lots of people are doing good things. Toronto has seen some good reductions. I wouldn't say there's any one that stands out as good at everything. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b"Coun. Doherty: Are there some municipalities in Ontario that you would hold up as best practices?\nSaxe: Lots of people are doing good things. Toronto has seen some good reductions. I wouldn't say there's any one that stands out as good at everything. #ygkc"

full_text:
Coun. Hutchison: Can you talk about building?
Saxe: We know that the carbon footprint is smaller in compact communities ppl. don't have to drive in. This can improve health, and benefit the environment. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b"Coun. Hutchison: Can you talk about building?\nSaxe: We know that the carbon footprint is smaller in compact communities ppl. don't have to drive in. This can improve health, and benefit the environment. #ygkc"

full_text:
Coun. Hutchison: You mentioned the cost of climate change on insurance. Do you have numbers for climate change costs on insurance across the province?
Saxe: I only have numbers I showed you...We know the cost is going up because of the disasters we see. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b'Coun. Hutchison: You mentioned the cost of climate change on insurance. Do you have numbers for climate change costs on insurance across the province?\nSaxe: I only have numbers I showed you...We know the cost is going up because of the disasters we see. #ygkc'

full_text:
Coun. Holland: Can you relate the impact of food production and emissions?
Saxe: I mentioned "Draw Down" during my presentation. We have huge opportunities on how we grow food, and use food...If you can't feed it to people or feed it to animals, put it back to the soil. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b'Coun. Holland: Can you relate the impact of food production and emissions?\nSaxe: I mentioned "Draw Down" during my presentation. We have huge opportunities on how we grow food, and use food...If you can\'t feed it to people or feed it to animals, put it back to the soil. #ygkc'

full_text:
Coun. Oosterhof: Is this the time to ask other levels of government/agencies about partnerships?
Saxe: First, you need a carbon budget. Determine what you need to do. Then look where to get the best bang for your buck. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b'Coun. Oosterhof: Is this the time to ask other levels of government/agencies about partnerships?\nSaxe: First, you need a carbon budget. Determine what you need to do. Then look where to get the best bang for your buck. #ygkc'

full_text:
Coun. Oosterhof: Is there one or two highlights from the rural areas that you can review with us?
Saxe: When ppl. produce lots of stormwater, they should pay for it. This money could be directed upstream (rural areas) to compensate landowners for holding water via wetlands. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b'Coun. Oosterhof: Is there one or two highlights from the rural areas that you can review with us?\nSaxe: When ppl. produce lots of stormwater, they should pay for it. This money could be directed upstream (rural areas) to compensate landowners for holding water via wetlands. #ygkc'

full_text:
Coun. McLaren: Is it possible we can do this without raising taxes?
Saxe: There are lots of different ways to think about it. But this is going to cost money. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b'Coun. McLaren: Is it possible we can do this without raising taxes?\nSaxe: There are lots of different ways to think about it. But this is going to cost money. #ygkc'

full_text:
Coun. Neill: Are bonds an option?
Saxe: There are emerging standards, and opportunities. #ygkc
full_text(utf-8): b'Coun. Neill: Are bonds an option?\nSaxe: There are emerging standards, and opportunities. #ygkc'

A: We have a commitment to Council that anytime we replace a vehicle we explore alternative options. With specialized vehicles, it is difficult to source.
